DISTRIBUTION AND HABITAT: As currently understood (Musser and Carleton, 1993), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1842" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[663,684,1425,1448]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[163,260,1455,1478]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">sciureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is broadly distributed in the Orinoco and Amazon river basins, through eastern and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[325,448,1513,1536]" name="Venezuela" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, the Guianas, northern and central 
<collectingCountry box="[357,431,1542,1565]" name="Brazil" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and Amazonian 
<collectingCountry name="Colombia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[265,363,1572,1595]" name="Ecuador" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, Peru´, and 
<collectingCountry box="[511,600,1572,1595]" name="Bolivia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. Specimens of this species are known only from the middle sections of the Rio Jurua´, up­ and downriver from the town of Eirunepe´. All specimens collected by us were taken in inundated grass patches along the river mar­ Amazonian populations allocated to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1842" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1210,193,216]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">sciureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characterized by a diploid number of 55 to 56.
</paragraph>
